." Man page for dp_message_add_thinking_part from libdisasterparty
.TH DP_MESSAGE_ADD_THINKING_PART 3 "August 09, 2025" "libdisasterparty @DP_VERSION@" "Disaster Party Manual"

.SH NAME
dp_message_add_thinking_part \- add a thinking content part to a Disaster Party message

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <disasterparty.h>
.PP
.BI "bool dp_message_add_thinking_part(dp_message_t *" message ", const char *" thinking ", const char *" signature ");"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B dp_message_add_thinking_part()
function adds a new content part of type
.B DP_CONTENT_PART_THINKING
to the specified
.I message
structure. This type of part is used to store or transmit the internal reasoning process of a model that supports "Thinking" tokens (e.g., Anthropic's Claude 3.7 Sonnet).

This is useful for preserving the full conversation history, including the model's hidden chain of thought, or for prefilling an assistant message with specific reasoning steps.

The function allocates memory for the part and copies the provided strings.

.TP
.I message
A pointer to the
.B dp_message_t
structure to which the part will be added.
.TP
.I thinking
The content of the thought process generated by the model.
.TP
.I signature
An optional string containing a cryptographic signature verifying the authenticity of the thinking block (specific to Anthropic's implementation). Can be NULL if not available or not required.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The function returns
.B true
if the part was successfully added, or
.B false
if memory allocation failed or if the message pointer was NULL.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dp_message (3),
.BR dp_request_config (3),
.BR dp_free_messages (3),
.BR disasterparty (7)
